---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout title="Privacy Policy" description="Kitchenote Privacy Policy. How we handle your data and protect your privacy.">

  <section class="py-16 md:py-24">
    <div class="container-narrow">
      <h1 class="mb-8">Privacy Policy</h1>

      <p class="text-neutral-500 mb-8">Last updated: January 2024</p>

      <div class="prose prose-neutral max-w-none">
        <h2>The short version</h2>
        <p>
          Your recipes are yours. We don't collect them, we don't sell them, we don't use them for advertising. They're stored on your device, period. Here's the full policy if you want the details.
        </p>

        <hr class="my-8" />

        <h2>1. Information We Collect</h2>

        <h3>Information you provide</h3>
        <p>
          If you contact us via email, we'll have your email address and whatever you share in your message. That's it. We don't require account creation, so we don't have usernames, passwords, or profile information.
        </p>

        <h3>Information collected automatically</h3>
        <p>
          We collect basic analytics to understand how people use Kitchenote:
        </p>
        <ul>
          <li>App opens and screen views (anonymized)</li>
          <li>Feature usage patterns (which features are popular)</li>
          <li>Crash reports and error logs</li>
          <li>Device type and iOS version</li>
        </ul>
        <p>
          This data is aggregated and anonymous—we can't identify individual users from it. We use privacy-friendly analytics that don't track you across apps or websites.
        </p>

        <h3>Information we don't collect</h3>
        <p>
          <strong>We do not have access to your recipes, collections, tags, or any content you create or save in the app.</strong> All of that data stays on your device. We can't see it, we can't access it, and we certainly can't sell it.
        </p>

        <h2>2. How We Use Information</h2>
        <p>The limited information we collect is used to:</p>
        <ul>
          <li>Respond to your support requests</li>
          <li>Understand how people use the app so we can make it better</li>
          <li>Fix bugs and improve stability</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>3. Information Sharing</h2>
        <p>
          We don't sell, rent, or trade your personal information. We may share anonymous, aggregated analytics with third parties (like "40% of users use Cook Mode"), but never individual data.
        </p>
        <p>
          We use the following third-party services:
        </p>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Analytics</strong>: For anonymous usage statistics</li>
          <li><strong>Crash reporting</strong>: To identify and fix bugs</li>
        </ul>
        <p>
          These services receive only the anonymous data described above.
        </p>

        <h2>4. Data Storage and Security</h2>
        <p>
          Your recipes and app data are stored locally on your device using iOS's secure storage. If you use iCloud backup, your data may be included in your device backup (managed by Apple, not by us).
        </p>
        <p>
          We don't operate servers that store your personal data. The only data we have is anonymous analytics, which is stored securely with our analytics provider.
        </p>

        <h2>5. Your Rights</h2>
        <p>You have the right to:</p>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Access</strong>: All your data is already on your device—you have full access</li>
          <li><strong>Delete</strong>: Delete the app and all local data is removed</li>
          <li><strong>Export</strong>: Export your recipes anytime using the app's export feature</li>
          <li><strong>Opt out of analytics</strong>: Contact us and we'll tell you how</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>6. Children's Privacy</h2>
        <p>
          Kitchenote is not directed at children under 13. We don't knowingly collect personal information from children. If you believe a child has provided us with personal information, please contact us.
        </p>

        <h2>7. Changes to This Policy</h2>
        <p>
          We may update this policy from time to time. If we make significant changes, we'll notify you through the app or by other means. Continued use after changes means you accept the new policy.
        </p>

        <h2>8. Contact Us</h2>
        <p>
          Questions about privacy? Email us at <a href="mailto:privacy@kitchenote.app">privacy@kitchenote.app</a>.
        </p>

        <hr class="my-8" />

        <p class="text-sm text-neutral-500">
          This policy was written in plain English because we believe you shouldn't need a law degree to understand how your data is handled.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

</Layout>

